    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the work of a family of painters, started by Kaiho Yusho, that lasted for seven generations until the end of the Edo period (1600-1868). Yusho's style was highly individualized and dramatic, typically wall screens.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
